Can't fight if you're not there.
That's what Gandhi taught us.

81
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:01,864
That's not true.

82
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:04,243
I can't believe that
Robin puts up with that.

83
00:04:04,626 --> 00:04:07,496
Don't worry. She's got a great way
to avoid fights, too.

84
00:04:09,302 --> 00:04:10,958
Are ties machine washable?

85
00:04:11,304 --> 00:04:13,749
No, they most certainly
are not. Why?

86
00:04:15,947 --> 00:04:17,131
What is in your hand?

87
00:04:18,133 --> 00:04:19,925
My God, what's in your hand?!

88
00:04:26,408 --> 00:04:29,463
Okay, so you walk away.
Robin gets naked.

89
00:04:29,588 --> 00:04:32,612
Those are the two stupidest ways
to handle conflict I've ever heard.

90
00:04:32,737 --> 00:04:34,273
The naked thing ain't bad.

91
00:04:35,922 --> 00:04:38,569
- That felt kind of weird.
- Okay, call me crazy.

92
00:04:39,072 --> 00:04:42,772
But when a problem comes up,
Lily and I actually talk about it.

93
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:45,269
There are so many great things to do
with the human mouth.

94
00:04:45,394 --> 00:04:46,924
Why waste it on talking?

95
00:04:47,049 --> 00:04:49,455
But if you insist,
here's what I would say

96
00:04:49,623 --> 00:04:51,957
about the dishes
if I were Lily's husband.

97
00:04:53,669 --> 00:04:55,169
Barney, you're home!

98
00:04:58,959 --> 00:04:59,715
Dude!

99
00:05:00,327 --> 00:05:02,051
- Get to the point!
- All right.

100
00:05:02,886 --> 00:05:04,036
Thanks, doll.

101
00:05:08,277 --> 00:05:09,975
Sweetie, are you going to wash that?

102
00:05:10,265 --> 00:05:12,227
I'm glad you bring that up. No.

103
00:05:12,659 --> 00:05:13,646
And here's why.

104
00:05:17,610 --> 00:05:20,016
Lily, I know you don't
like a dirty sink.

105
00:05:20,141 --> 00:05:22,029
But does that make it my job
to keep it clean?

106
00:05:22,507 --> 00:05:25,275
I mean, if one day I look up
at the living room ceiling

107
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:28,354
and think, "Hey, I'd like a replica
of the Sistine Chapel up there."

108
00:05:28,479 --> 00:05:30,424
Would it be your job to paint it?

109
00:05:30,549 --> 00:05:31,872
No.
Of course not.

110
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:34,360
Exactly! So, baby,
by the same logic,

111
00:05:34,485 --> 00:05:36,546
if you don't like looking
at a sink full of dishes,

112
00:05:36,671 --> 00:05:38,379
shouldn't it be your job
to clean them?

113
00:05:40,140 --> 00:05:43,102
Thanks for explaining that.
I get so confused.

114
00:05:43,718 --> 00:05:45,427
That's because you're a woman.

115
00:05:48,098 --> 00:05:51,016
- I don't even know why we're laughing!
- Of course you don't.

116
00:05:54,392 --> 00:05:55,854
