Barney Stinson's circus tent

131
00:06:42,437 --> 00:06:44,248
of funhouse mirrors
and flawed logic.

132
00:06:44,373 --> 00:06:46,572
This is exactly how you
got the earring back in '03.

133
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:49,283
- That earring looked cool.
- It did look cool, didn't it?

134
00:06:49,638 --> 00:06:52,001
Stay with me!
Barney is wrong.

135
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:54,580
No, he isn't.

136
00:06:55,916 --> 00:06:57,883
I hate doing my dishes right away.

137
00:06:58,008 --> 00:07:00,377
- You just said you don't mind!
- I hate it, Ted!

138
00:07:00,786 --> 00:07:03,114
I hate it with a boundless,
burning fury!

139
00:07:03,239 --> 00:07:06,091
I hate it, I hate it, I hate it!

140
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:07,389
You're welcome.

141
00:07:07,514 --> 00:07:08,385
Hey, guys.

142
00:07:09,101 --> 00:07:10,554
Good.
There you are.

143
00:07:10,828 --> 00:07:14,391
You'll tell me the truth.
Barney says that you two never fight.

144
00:07:15,416 --> 00:07:17,436
- I guess that's true.
- Told ya.

145
00:07:17,804 --> 00:07:20,101
No way.
I love you both,

146
00:07:20,226 --> 00:07:22,443
but you are the two most
emotionally ill-equipped

147
00:07:22,568 --> 00:07:24,630
individuals in the history
of relationships.

148
00:07:24,755 --> 00:07:26,570
You two must have had
at least one fight.

149
00:07:26,820 --> 00:07:28,447
You know what?
We did.

150
00:07:29,259 --> 00:07:30,680
There was one small dispute

151
00:07:30,805 --> 00:07:32,785
about which one of
us was more awesome.

152
00:07:32,953 --> 00:07:34,858
We just called it
a tie Sand had sex.

153
00:07:35,840 --> 00:07:38,953
Speaking of which, I am so glad
we're going skiing this weekend.

154
00:07:39,078 --> 00:07:41,919
I need a break. The upstairs neighbors
are driving me crazy.

155
00:07:42,087 --> 00:07:43,295
Yeah, it's bad.

156
00:07:43,576 --> 00:07:45,839
- I'm gonna say something to them.
- Thank you.

157
00:07:46,007 --> 00:07:47,965
We all have our assignments
for the weekend.

158
00:07:48,090 --> 00:07:51,284
Ted, you're going to stand up to
your neighbors and you to Lily.

159
00:07:51,409 --> 00:07:53,846
Robin, I'm gonna need you
in sort of a crouched position

160
00:07:53,971 --> 00:07:56,453
on the bear-skin rug
at our ski chalet. Ready?

161
00:07:56,838 --> 00:07:58,398
- Bye, guys.
- Bye.

162
00:07:58,523 --> 00:07:59,853
Have fun.

163
00:08:02,859 --> 00:08:03,752
You know?

164
00:08:03,877 --> 00:08:06,342
With his crazy, well-
thought-out theories

165
00:08:06,467 --> 00:08:07,877
